definition.value: A member of the class of phenylacetic acids that is phenylacetic acid in which the phenyl grup is substituted at the ortho- position by a nitro group.

A phosphate-linked oligosaccharide analogue consisting of six alpha-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl residues, joined by (1->4)-phosphodiester linkages. It is a constituent 6-repeating-unit segment of Neisseria meningitidis serogroup X capsular polysaccharide (MenX), the structural diagram of which shows parts of phosphodiester linkages which are present at both the reducing and non-reducing ends of the hexasaccharide unit.

A phosphate-linked oligosaccharide analogue consisting of seven alpha-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl residues, joined by (1->4)-phosphodiester linkages. It is a constituent 7-repeating-unit segment of Neisseria meningitidis serogroup X capsular polysaccharide (MenX), the structural diagram of which shows parts of phosphodiester linkages which are present at both the reducing and non-reducing ends of the heptasaccharide unit.
A carboxamidinium ion obtained by protonation of  the amidino group of benzamidine. Major species at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of baclofen.

A glycopentaosylceramide having beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl component attached to the primary hydroxy function of a ceramide with undefined sphingoid base.
A phenol substituted at position 4 by a 2-hydroxyethyl group.
A flavonoid oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the hydroxy group at position 7 of the flavone moiety of quercetin. The major species at pH 7.3.
